preview_comments.text:
My video #13 in this link,
https://youtu.be/wWjI6q26v_4,
especially discusses the ONLY 'retroflexed' form of pinyin.
It also completes my videos #10 & #12 in detailing the use of different pinyin alphabets, in respect to the different following vowel alphabet, for the same pronunciation of English sound 'ch', 'j' or 's', respectively. So many Mandarin Lectures need extra attention to this subject matter as not a few of foreign students are confused about it.
Foreign students are commonly trapped with the notion of alphabet i in pinyin pronunciation. That complete video set of  #11, #12 & #13, indeed helps clarifying the issue in scientific way so is very easy for the students to understand.
Please subscribe, view and like it. You may freely share it to anybody who is interested in the topic.
https://youtube.com/channel/UCZFzbDmicRr8BC2S3qFIFaw
Thanks
